  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coopaba vers une coop&#xE9;rative professionnelle</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Achat de   2 balance plate-forme
       Achat de 1 Humidim&#xE8;tre &#xE0; grain 
       &#xC9;coles champs paysan et pratique de la Gestion Integr&#xE9;e de la Fertilit&#xE9; des Sols (GIFS)
       S&#xE9;ances d&apos;information des membres du contrat   riz et campagnes de mobilisation   des non-membres &#xE0; rejoindre la cooperative. 
       R&#xE9;vision du MAPAF   (manuel de procedures administratives et financi&#xE8;res) 
       Achat d&apos;un modem   pour acces internet + frais mensuel de communication et achat Microsoft   Office + papeterie bureau (+ laptop occasion d&apos;Agriterra)
       Atelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan   strat&#xE9;gique (plan financier inclus)
       Atelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan   d&apos;affaire (+plan de tr&#xE9;sorerie et plan des   operations)
       Am&#xE9;lioration de la comptabilit&#xE9; en Excel et pr&#xE9;paration des &#xE9;tats financiers
       Suivi du contrat   et des livraisons &#xE0; Bralima</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">COOPABA is one of the 5 cooperatives participating in the Ruzizi Rice Project 18at-8092. COOPABA  is a young cooperative structure of about six years with many ambitions of transformation and marketing of agricultural products. Created to meet the critical needs of members in difficult access to the remunerative market and the sale of raw agricultural products. This young cooperative holds by various strategies defined to penetrate the industrial market of Bralima through the support of Agriterra and to work on the quality of table rice. To this end  COOPABA is resolutely committed to improving production through the strategy of grouping its grassroots members into associative groups and exploiting model fields in each grouping where the new farming methods and techniques will be made to to encourage members to increase their production. The efforts made by a total of 114 potential member producers and 8 agents sufficiently prove the commitment of this cooperative to meet the needs of the market that Agriterra had just negotiated with the Bralima for the agricultural producers of the Ruzizi plain. in general and for those of COOPABA in particular.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cooperative would like to  professionalize in the activity of collecting and selling rice of its members  in order to make it more profitable. So  they can earn more income and sell large quantities of quality rice to the Bralima.</narrative>
  </description>
